title: Ocean Memories
date: "2025-07-07"
description: "Reflections on the sea and time"
---

# Ocean Memories

Waves crash upon the weathered shore,
Eternal rhythm, ancient song.
Memories carried in the foam,
Of where I've been, where I belong.

Salt-tinged air fills my lungs,
As distant ships cross the line
Where azure meets the endless sky,
In that perfect, seamless design.

I trace my fingers through the sand,
Creating patterns soon erased.
Just as time washes clean our past,
And futures yet to be embraced.

Seashells scattered at my feet,
Once homes to creatures of the deep.
Now empty vessels, smooth and worn,
Their secrets they forever keep.

The ocean holds no grudges here,
It simply ebbs and simply flows.
Accepting what the world provides,
Releasing what it no longer knows.

I stand at edge of land and sea,
Where certainty meets mystery.
And in this space between two worlds,
I find my own true history.
